April 04, 2003
My sister came into my life. I remember being the happiest around her since then. I remember asking my Mom and dad so often that when would I have a sibling and they would always have the same reply.. “ Jab tum fridge jitni badi ho jaaogi “

December 24, 2023
Manvi left us all. We are still unable to process it.  She was the baby of the house and all 3 of us - mom, dad and me, we could never say no to her for anything. 
From discussions over guys on her Hinge to brainstorming sessions over my shoots and her UNICEF meetings, there was no single thing we didn’t share with each other. I used to call her my WAZIR. She was the one who would give me the strength to get up again and walk when I was just about to give up. We would have our crying sessions too where we could rant about random stuff. From educating me about Gen Z slangs to helping me grow as an individual, from helping me plan my outfits for an event to discussing about our future goals. Manvi was an extraordinary person who brought so much light to our lives. 
Things I have to say are never ending. So I guess I need to conclude and just say - I love you Manvaaaa. We miss you.❤️
